  "interpretation": {
    "deck_reading": "A 52-card deck has the same cardinality as the certified quotient. The invariant here is Z/2 x Z/26, equivalently a 2-primary square times a 13-line; no suit/rank labelling is canonical yet.",
    "strict_weak_order_reading": "The 13 strict weak orderings of three labelled elements are a good candidate for the ternary-comparison logic behind the ledger, because they are exactly the transitive part of the 3^3 pairwise ternary comparison cube. This certificate only proves numerical compatibility.",
